decks.notes: This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's strategy with disruptive spells like Thoughtseize, while also applying pressure with aggressive creatures like Boggart Trawler and Ketramose, the New Dawn. It utilizes cards like Flickerwisp and Ephemerate to gain additional value from entering the battlefield abilities, and uses cards like Prismatic Ending and Fatal Push to handle threats. The deck also includes graveyard hate with Relic of Progenitus and powerful finishers like Emperor of Bones and Overlord of the Balemurk. The mana base is designed to support the deck's color requirements while providing flexibility in fetching lands.

The core idea of this deck is to ramp up mana quickly, utilizing cards like Farseek, Arboreal Grazer, and Green Sun's Zenith to accelerate the game towards a win condition centered around Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle. By playing lands like Wooded Foothills and Misty Rainforest, the deck can trigger Valakut's ability multiple times in a turn with cards like Scapeshift, dealing massive amounts of damage to the opponent and potentially winning the game in one explosive turn. Additionally, cards like Primeval Titan and Titania, Protector of Argoth provide additional threats and synergies to keep the opponent on their toes.

This Boros Aggro deck is focused on quickly overwhelming the opponent with a mix of aggressive creatures and powerful burn spells. The deck aims to establish early board presence with efficient creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Guide of Souls, while also preventing the opponent from mounting a strong defense with cards like Static Prison. By utilizing cards like Goblin Bombardment and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, the deck can quickly close out games before the opponent has a chance to stabilize. The deck's mix of fast creatures, burn spells, and disruptive elements make it a formidable force in Modern 1 vs 1 matchups.
